(23, 'How to Build a Balanced Plate: A Simple Guide to Healthy Eating', '                            <p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Eating a balanced diet is essential for maintaining good health, sustaining energy levels, and preventing chronic diseases. A well-structured plate helps ensure you get the right nutrients in the right proportions.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Key Components of a Balanced Plate</h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">1. Vegetables (Half of Your Plate)</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Fill half of your plate with a variety of colorful vegetables. They are rich in vitamins, minerals, fiber, and antioxidants that support overall health.</p><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Leafy greens (spinach, kale, lettuce)</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Cruciferous vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts)</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Colorful veggies (carrots, bell peppers, tomatoes, zucchini)</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">2. Lean Proteins (One-Quarter of Your Plate)</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Protein is essential for muscle growth, repair, and overall body function. Include a mix of plant-based and animal-based proteins.</p><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Lean meats (chicken, turkey, fish)</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Plant-based proteins (beans, lentils, tofu, tempeh)</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Eggs and dairy (Greek yogurt, cottage cheese)</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">3. Whole Grains (One-Quarter of Your Plate)</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Whole grains provide fiber, essential vitamins, and long-lasting energy.</p><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Brown rice, quinoa, whole wheat bread, oats</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Whole grain pasta, barley, millet</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">4. Healthy Fats (In Moderation)</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Healthy fats support brain function, heart health, and hormone balance.</p><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Avocados, nuts, seeds</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Olive oil, flaxseeds, chia seeds</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Fatty fish (salmon, sardines, mackerel)</li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Tips for Creating a Balanced Plate</h2><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Portion Control: Use smaller plates and measure portions to avoid overeating.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Variety: Rotate different vegetables, proteins, and grains to get diverse nutrients.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Mindful Eating: Eat slowly, enjoy your food, and listen to your body\'s hunger cues.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Hydration: Drink plenty of water throughout the day.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Limit Processed Foods: Choose whole, unprocessed foods whenever possible.</li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Final Thoughts</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Building a balanced plate is an easy way to improve your diet and overall well-being. By following these simple guidelines, you can ensure that your meals are nutritious, satisfying, and beneficial for long-term health.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Need personalized nutrition advice? Consult a certified dietitian for a meal plan tailored to your needs!</p>                                                                                      ', 'jpg', 6, '2026-01-15', '2026-02-09', 0),
(24, 'The Role of Gut Health in Weight Management', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Maintaining a&nbsp;healthy weight&nbsp;isn’t just about&nbsp;calories in vs. calories out—your&nbsp;gut health&nbsp;plays a crucial role in metabolism, digestion, and fat storage. A well-balanced gut microbiome can aid weight loss, while an imbalanced gut can lead to weight gain and metabolic issues.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">How Gut Health Affects Weight</h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">1. Gut Bacteria and Metabolism</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Your gut is home to&nbsp;trillions of bacteria&nbsp;that help break down food, absorb nutrients, and regulate fat storage. An imbalance in gut bacteria (dysbiosis) can lead to&nbsp;slower metabolism and increased fat accumulation.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">2. Impact on Hunger and Cravings</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Certain gut bacteria influence&nbsp;hormones like ghrelin (hunger hormone) and leptin (satiety hormone). A healthy gut helps regulate these hormones, reducing cravings and overeating.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">3. Inflammation and Weight Gain</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">An unhealthy gut triggers&nbsp;chronic inflammation, which is linked to&nbsp;insulin resistance and obesity. Inflammation can make it harder for the body to burn fat effectively.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">4. Gut-Brain Connection</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Your gut and brain communicate through the&nbsp;gut-brain axis. Poor gut health can lead to stress and emotional eating, making weight management more challenging.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Best Foods for a Healthy Gut and Weight Loss</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Including&nbsp;gut-friendly foods&nbsp;in your diet can improve digestion and support weight management:</p><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Probiotic Foods&nbsp;(Boost Good Bacteria): Yogurt, kefir, kimchi, sauerkraut, miso, tempeh</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Prebiotic Foods&nbsp;(Feed Good Bacteria): Bananas, garlic, onions, asparagus, oats, flaxseeds</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">High-Fiber Foods&nbsp;(Improve Digestion &amp; Satiety): Leafy greens, legumes, whole grains, chia seeds</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Anti-Inflammatory Foods&nbsp;(Reduce Gut Inflammation): Turmeric, ginger, green tea, fatty fish (salmon, mackerel)</li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Tips for Improving Gut Health for Weight Loss</h2><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Eat a Diverse Diet&nbsp;– More variety in plant-based foods means a more diverse gut microbiome.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Stay Hydrated&nbsp;– Water supports digestion and helps transport nutrients efficiently.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Limit Processed Foods &amp; Sugar&nbsp;– These can promote harmful bacteria and increase inflammation.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Manage Stress&nbsp;– Chronic stress can harm gut bacteria and lead to weight gain.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Get Enough Sleep&nbsp;– Poor sleep disrupts gut bacteria and hunger hormones.</li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Final Thoughts</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">A&nbsp;healthy gut&nbsp;is the key to&nbsp;better digestion, improved metabolism, and effective weight management. If you’re struggling with weight loss, focusing on&nbsp;gut-friendly nutrition&nbsp;can be a game-changer.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Looking for a personalized gut health diet plan?&nbsp;Consult a&nbsp;certified dietitian&nbsp;today!</p>', 'jpg', 2, '2026-01-15', '2026-01-15', 0),
(25, '10 Superfoods Every Woman Should Include in Her Diet', '                            <p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">A balanced diet plays a crucial role in&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" style=\"transition: 0.5s ease-in-out;\">women’s health</span>, supporting&nbsp;hormonal balance, bone strength, heart health, and overall well-being. Including nutrient-dense superfoods can help prevent deficiencies and promote long-term vitality.</p><ul style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">1. Leafy Greens (Spinach, Kale, Fenugreek)&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Rich in&nbsp;iron, calcium, folate, and fiber, essential for bone health, blood circulation, and digestion.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">2. Berries (Blueberries, Strawberries, Raspberries)&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">High in&nbsp;antioxidants and vitamin C, great for skin, immunity, and heart health.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">3. Fatty Fish (Salmon, Mackerel, Sardines)&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Packed with&nbsp;omega-3 fatty acids, supporting brain function, inflammation reduction, and heart health.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">4. Greek Yogurt&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Loaded with&nbsp;calcium and probiotics&nbsp;for strong bones and gut health.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">5. Nuts &amp; Seeds (Almonds, Walnuts, Flaxseeds, Chia Seeds)&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Excellent for&nbsp;hormonal balance, energy, and skin health.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">6. Avocados&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Rich in&nbsp;healthy fats&nbsp;that support heart and hormonal health.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">7. Eggs&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Full of&nbsp;protein, choline, and biotin, supporting brain health and metabolism.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">8. Legumes (Lentils, Chickpeas, Beans)&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Plant-based protein for&nbsp;muscle repair and digestion.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">9. Turmeric&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Contains&nbsp;curcumin, which has anti-inflammatory and immune-boosting properties.</p></li><li><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">10. Sweet Potatoes&nbsp;</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\">Great source of&nbsp;fiber and vitamin A, beneficial for energy and skin health.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Final Thoughts</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Including these&nbsp;superfoods&nbsp;in your daily diet can&nbsp;<span class=\"highlight\" style=\"transition: 0.5s ease-in-out;\">boost immunity, regulate hormones, and enhance overall health</span>. For a personalized meal plan, consult a&nbsp;certified dietitian&nbsp;today!</p>                                                                                      ', 'jpg', 9, '2026-01-15', '2026-01-15', 0),
(26, 'The Importance of Hydration: How Water Impacts Your Health and Wellness', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Water is essential for life, and staying hydrated is crucial for maintaining overall health and well-being. Proper hydration supports various bodily functions and helps prevent dehydration-related health issues.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Why Hydration is Important</h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">1. Supports Vital Body Functions</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Water plays a key role in digestion, circulation, temperature regulation, and waste elimination.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">2. Boosts Energy and Brain Function</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Even mild dehydration can lead to fatigue, headaches, and difficulty concentrating.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">3. Aids Digestion and Nutrient Absorption</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Water helps break down food and transport nutrients throughout the body.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">4. Promotes Healthy Skin</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Proper hydration keeps your skin moisturized and helps maintain a youthful appearance.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 35px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px !important;\">5. Supports Weight Management</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Drinking water before meals can help control appetite and prevent overeating.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">How Much Water Should You Drink?</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The general recommendation is to drink at least 8 cups (2 liters) of water per day, but individual needs may vary based on age, activity level, and climate.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Tips for Staying Hydrated</h2><ul class=\"g-list\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Carry a reusable water bottle and sip throughout the day.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Eat water-rich foods like fruits and vegetables.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Drink water before, during, and after exercise.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Limit dehydrating beverages like alcohol and sugary drinks.</li><li style=\"margin-left: 55.75px; list-style: disc !important;\">Listen to your body and drink when thirsty.</li></ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 40px; color: rgb(43, 52, 59); font-family: Prata, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 25px !important;\">Final Thoughts</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Hydration is essential for maintaining energy, focus, and overall health. Make drinking water a daily habit to support your body’s needs and enhance your well-being.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; color: rgb(134, 137, 140); font-family: lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Need personalized hydration tips?&nbsp;Consult a certified dietitian to optimize your water intake!</p>                                      ', 'jpg', 11, '2026-01-15', '2026-01-15', 0),
